---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import StatPanel from '@/components/StatPanel.astro';

const headlineStats = [
  { label: 'Participating teams', value: '137', note: 'NoEscape CTF 2022' },
  { label: 'Participants', value: '400+', note: 'from 25+ countries' },
  { label: 'CTFtime weight', value: '20.17', note: 'first-run event rating' },
  { label: 'Core team', value: '2', note: 'organizers' },
];

const teamStats = [
  { label: 'Team', value: 'F7 Conquerors', note: 'CTFtime team 206244' },
  { label: 'India rank (current)', value: '#87', note: '2026 year-to-date' },
  { label: 'India rank (best)', value: '#20', note: '2016–2017' },
  { label: 'Events, all time', value: '60+', note: 'across team history' },
];

// CTFs the team played while I was involved (2022–2023)
const eventsCompeted = [
  { year: 2023, name: 'CSAW CTF Qualification Round', weight: '23.76' },
  { year: 2023, name: 'COMPFEST CTF', weight: '14.45' },
  { year: 2022, name: 'ASIS CTF Finals', weight: '93.32' },
  { year: 2022, name: 'X-MAS CTF', weight: '24.34' },
  { year: 2022, name: 'ISITDTU CTF 2022 Quals', weight: '40.70' },
  { year: 2022, name: 'MetaRed International CTF', weight: '35.21' },
  { year: 2022, name: 'p4ctf 2022', weight: '57.74' },
  { year: 2022, name: 'EKOPARTY CTF 2022', weight: '50.00' },
];

const profiles = [
  {
    name: 'CTFtime — Team F7 Conquerors',
    href: 'https://ctftime.org/team/206244',
    handle: 'team 206244',
  },
  {
    name: 'CTFtime — NoEscape CTF 2022 (organized)',
    href: 'https://ctftime.org/event/1822/',
    handle: 'event 1822 · jeopardy · online+onsite',
  },
  {
    name: 'NoEscape CTF archive',
    href: 'https://noescape.live/',
    handle: 'noescape.live',
  },
  {
    name: 'GitHub',
    href: 'https://github.com/NikkyAmresh',
    handle: '@NikkyAmresh',
  },
  {
    name: 'LinkedIn',
    href: 'https://linkedin.com/in/nikky-amresh',
    handle: 'nikky-amresh',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Security & CTFs"
  description="Cybersecurity work and CTF history — organizing NoEscape CTF 2022, team F7 Conquerors, SIH 2022 Grand Finale, and more."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prose px-4 pb-20 pt-12 sm:px-6 sm:pt-16 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <header>
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Security &amp; CTFs</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Cybersecurity is how I got into code.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
        Before I was writing backend systems, I was breaking them. I ran my first CTF challenge
        in college, got hooked, ended up on a team, and eventually co-organized one of my own.
        That background shapes how I write production software now — I assume things break, I
        look for the boundary conditions, and I don&rsquo;t trust inputs.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- NECTF feature -->
    <section class="mt-14">
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-text-subtle">Feature</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
        NoEscape CTF 2022
        <span class="text-text-subtle">/</span>
        <span class="font-mono text-base text-text-muted">NECTF</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted">
        A jeopardy-style international CTF organized out of Roorkee Institute of Technology in November 2022.
        Two-person core team. 24-hour online event with a parallel onsite component — 137 teams registered on
        CTFtime, 400+ active participants from 25+ countries competing on challenges in web, pwn, forensics,
        steganography, crypto, OSINT, and trivia.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <StatPanel stats={headlineStats} />
      </div>

      <p class="mt-8 text-text-muted">
        The hard part wasn&rsquo;t writing challenges. It was everything else: infrastructure that
        didn&rsquo;t collapse under load, scoring and flag-submission that worked under partitions,
        a communications plan for 25+ time zones, and judging escalations at 3 AM. I learned more
        about running reliable systems from that weekend than from most production incidents since.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <a href="https://ctftime.org/event/1822/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent no-underline hover:underline underline-offset-4">
          CTFtime event →
        </a>
        <a href="https://noescape.live/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent no-underline hover:underline underline-offset-4">
          noescape.live →
        </a>
        <a href="https://blog.aravindha.in/noescape-live/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent no-underline hover:underline underline-offset-4">
          A competitor writeup →
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Team -->
    <section class="mt-16">
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-text-subtle">Team</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">F7 Conquerors</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted">
        I&rsquo;ve competed and organized with F7 Conquerors — an India-based CTF team active on
        CTFtime since 2012. My active era was 2022–2023, around NECTF and the finals/quals
        listed below.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <StatPanel stats={teamStats} />
      </div>

      <p class="mt-6 text-xs text-text-subtle">
        Stats pulled from CTFtime (team 206244). Ranks are country-wide (India); the team has peaked at India #20 in 2016–2017.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Events list -->
    <section class="mt-16">
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-text-subtle">Competed</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
        CTFs I&rsquo;ve played
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted">
        A curated set during my active era — skewed toward international high-weight events.
      </p>

      <ul class="mt-8 divide-y divide-border border-y border-border">
        {
          eventsCompeted.map((e) => (
            <li class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4 py-3 text-sm">
              <span class="text-text">{e.name}</span>
              <span class="flex items-baseline gap-3 text-text-subtle">
                <span class="font-mono">w&nbsp;{e.weight}</span>
                <span class="font-mono text-xs">{e.year}</span>
              </span>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- SIH 2022 -->
    <section class="mt-16">
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-text-subtle">Hackathon</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
        Smart India Hackathon 2022 — Grand Finale
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted">
        Built <strong class="font-medium text-text">Verifi</strong>, an offline OTP authentication
        system, for a DRDO problem statement. The challenge was real: field authentication in
        environments where connectivity is adversarial or absent. We designed a scheme that
        worked with seeded secrets + time-based derivation, no live server call required.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-text-muted">
        The project made it to the Grand Finale — the top shortlist out of thousands of
        participating teams nationally.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Profiles -->
    <section class="mt-16">
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-text-subtle">Profiles</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">Go dig</h2>

      <ul class="mt-8 divide-y divide-border border-y border-border">
        {
          profiles.map((p) => (
            <li>
              <a
                href={p.href}
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="group flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4 py-3 no-underline transition hover:bg-bg-subtle"
              >
                <span class="text-sm text-text group-hover:text-accent">{p.name}</span>
                <span class="font-mono text-xs text-text-subtle">
                  {p.handle}
                  <span class="ml-1 inline-block translate-x-0 opacity-0 transition group-hover:translate-x-0.5 group-hover:opacity-100">
                    →
                  </span>
                </span>
              </a>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Back link -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <a href="/" class="font-mono text-sm text-accent no-underline hover:underline underline-offset-4">
        ← Back to home
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
